5000|$|A <b>spoolbase</b> is a shore-based {{facility}} used {{to facilitate}} continuous pipe laying for offshore {{oil and gas}} production. The facility allows the welding of single or double joints (40' or 80') of steel pipe of 4" [...] to 18" [...] diameter, into predetermined lengths for spooling onto a reel lay vessel.|$|E
50|$|Shore based <b>spoolbases</b> {{serve the}} oil and gas sector from {{locations}} in the USA, UK, Norway, Brazil, and Angola, and portable <b>spoolbases</b> may be set up in any location to suit local requirements.|$|R

